div.p:
As I deduce your position, it would be that:
—we should let Waldheim carry the main brunt of the argument with the Turks now;
—we should not give the Turks the impression we are ganging up against them;
—we could talk to the Turks when the new government gets its feet on the ground about avoiding isolation when the Security Council debate nears;
—we can take a straightforward position, as we have for some time, of favoring intercommunal talks as long as we can do so in a low-key way without putting ourselves in open opposition to the Turks.
